com.garmin.health

Interface PairingCallback


  • public interface PairingCallback
    Pairing result is reported using these callbacks.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void authRequested(AuthCompletion completion)
      Called when a Device needs a passkey to establish a connection.
      default void authTimeout()
      Called when a authentication times out, no need to retry here, if a retry is available it will be triggered through authFailed userCallback.
      void pairingFailed(PairingFailedException cause)
      Called if pairing fails.
      void pairingSucceeded(Device device)
      Called when the pairing process completes successfully.

      • authTimeout

        default void authTimeout()
        Called when a authentication times out, no need to retry here, if a retry is available it will be triggered through authFailed userCallback.
